Proud member of DRAKONIS and TGA<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.TunareGuildAlliance.org/guilds/drakonis_logo.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xasam>xasam</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/2/03 9:23:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4772.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Windblade or Wavecrasher/Frosty</span><hr size=1> I have a Windblade and also Wavecrasher/Frosty.  When I am in XP groups in the planes I definitely notice the difference in aggro when using the Windblade.  The mobs peel off for the casters twice as often when I am using the Windblade than they do with WC/FB.  For that reason I bag the Windblade when I am MT (and I beg others to MT so I can use it, cause I love it so).  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=182847">Xasam</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> 59 Warrior Quellious <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=akamekministud>akamek ministud</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/4/03 11:42:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4772.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   windblade</span><hr size=1> A windblade would up your dps and your aggro should be just fine.  However if your still worried about aggro then imo you could sell your jade mace and seb dirk.  That would get you probably about 8-9k on Prexus.  From there buy a guard captains mallet which is 2-3k on Prexus, you'll have around 5k to ad to your Windblade savings.  Thats just my 2cp but it's your money and equip so do what you feel is best.  <br>
                                  Akamek Ministud <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=brutultarewmarr>Brutul Tarew Marr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Slayer of Whiners</span><br>  Posts: 987<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/5/03 2:16:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4772.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.blackcompany.cc/member_pics/45.jpg height=185 width=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: windblade</span><hr size=1> If you're duoing with a cleric you shouldn't have horrible Aggro problems unless you're getting beat up on the pulls and the cleric has to heal early.  That combo is also a little light on DPS, so I'd say go for the windblade. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=325267">Brutul Vilesilencer</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://images.allposters.com/images/54/039_15016.jpg">Barbarian</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> Overlord of the <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.blackcompany.cc">Black Company</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.realpoor.com">Tarew Marr</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=baadan>Baadan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.imahosting.com/sigs/posticon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 468<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/5/03 10:24:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4772.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: windblade</span><hr size=1> I didn't really understand the last part of your post Xasam, but are you saying that a Windblade is better aggro (and dps) than a Wavecrasher/Frosty combo??<br>
<br>
I am considering both of these options but I can only afford one and not both (have ~55k to spend, windblade is ~35k, wc/fb is ~25k)<br>
<br>
WC/FB seems like a very solid combo to me..I mean 20% in one hand and a DD and AC debuff in the other...but I have been hearing very good things about the Windblade.<br>
<br>
Also I'm level 52, the Windblade is 46/44 for me.<br>
<br>
What does it take to get a better weapon than the Windblade, in the same price range? (~35k on mith marr for the cheap ones) I am always atleast 42% hasted atm (schw + EoP) <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=168211" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.imahosting.com/sigs/baadsignew.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:Verdana;font-size:medium;">{52 Champion} <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=168211" target="top">Baadan</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> (Half Elf) &lt;<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub11.ezboard.com/bdragonmawguild" target="top">Dragon Maw</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->&gt;</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->{37 Necromancer} <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=115139" target="top">Azumaan</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> (Erudite) &lt;<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub11.ezboard.com/bdragonmawguild" target="top">Dragon Maw</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->&gt; </div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=baadan>Baadan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.imahosting.com/sigs/posticon.gif" BORDER=0> at: 1/8/03 4:57:19 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=artistikone>Artistikone</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/7/03 10:31:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4772.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: windblade</span><hr size=1> If you duo alot then I would suggest picking up a ToD and Dismay Axe. The ToD is good dps until slow procs, then easily swap the Dismay for added dps. I wouldn't recommend going to the planes at 53 unless your cleric is 59-60 with a huge mana pool. Even at 60 w/ a 58 shm 2 boxing it wasn't easy. It's more efficient for you to stay in pre-pop content and slaughter the low dark blues, pop mobs hit to hard/too much without a slower. In a duo situation, I would concentrate on your DPS over aggro, since your the only dps, and aggro shouldnt be a problem(if it is, move to weaker mobs). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tiejinnie>Tiejinnie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 157<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/7/03 10:35:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4772.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://homex.coolconnect.com/member3/Tiejinnie/images/Avatar.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: windblade</span><hr size=1> The reason why many ppl say Windblade is better than WC/FB combo is pretty simple.<br>
<br>
With the Windblade, you are talking about dishing out straight DPS.<br>
<br>
With the WC/FB combo, you are dependant on the proc(s) to gain aggro. Without any firm guarantee that the proc(s) will come in early, there is also no firm guarantee that you will hold aggro, and without procs, the combo dishes out pretty pathetic DPS.<br>
<br>
The Windblade would prolly be more consistent in maintaining aggro early and late in the fight, as compared with WC/FB combo. <p>- Tiejinnie: 65 Overlord -<br>
