It is a 14/24 1hs that weighs 0.5 and procs a 200 DoT poison over 30 seconds and a 30 DD. it generates alot of agro. Coupled with the Frosty you already have it is a solid 1hs combo that will always keep agro.<br>
The problem is the blade is really rare as it was pulled off the drop list about 4 months after Kunark came out. On my server there are estimated to be 6 in existence. The sword is a powerful agro producer after level 50. Procs on average at least once per mob and I have seen as many as 8-9 procs a single mob.<br>
Not sure which server you are on, on my server these are worth 45-50kpp.<br>
What the other guy was saying about the Windblade is that he found while using it the casters were able to peel mobs off him more easily than when he used his 1hs combo.<br>
DPS is one thing, but constantly hitting a mob generates more agro in my opinion, particularily if you are swinging 2 proc weapons. Remember tho that mobs tend to dislike procs that effect them for longer periods of time and virtually ignore the procs that only do Direct Damage.<br>
Yet, Fleshgrinders are nice agro weapons as they hit reasonable hard at 12 damage and fast at 19 delay. The proc is a 160 DD.<br>
The other thing to consider is the types of classes you generally group with. For example, if you were consistently grouping with a Shaman or Chanter that slowed the mobs for you, I guarantee that you would find the wavecrasher to be useless for agro. Once a mob is slowed the proc from the wavecrasher ( a 20% slow ) is automatically resisted because the other classes slows are higher in level. Therefore the mobs Ignore the wavecrasher's proc making it useless. Additionally, I have never liked that the wavecrasher is Primary only. The wavecrasher is a vastly over rated weapon and no where near worth the price.<br>
Good luck in your decision.<br>
